DURBAN – Pietermaritzburg police are looking for witnesses in a hit-and-run accident that left a woman critically injured in January. KZN police said the victim Duduzile Doris Khumalo, 43, had been walking along Bambatha Road (New Greytown Road) near Prilla Mills Factory in Pietermaritzburg, on January 28 at around 4 pm when she was allegedly struck from behind by a vehicle. "The vehicle did not stop after the accident and the driver did not report the collision to any police station. "The injured woman was taken to hospital in a critical condition," said Lt Colonel Thulani Zwane. He said a case of reckless and negligent driving was opened at Mountain Rise SAPS further investigation. "Mountain Rise detectives are appealing to members of the community to assist with any information that will assist them in solving the case." Anyone with information with regards to the identity of the driver or who witnessed the accident is requested to contact the investigating officer, Detective Warrant Officer Subendran Pillay on 073 167 1865/033 3879682 or Crime Stop on 08600 10111. Daily News